    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "What about\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.hitsPerPageSelector({\n    container: '#hits-per-page-selector',\n    options: [\n      {value: 10, label: '10 results'},\n      {value: 50, label: '50 results'},\n      {value: 100, label: '100 results'},\n    ]\n  })\n);\n```\n\nThis would map `<select><option></option></select>` and avoid repeating `hitsPerPage`.\n\nHmm but indexSelector has a similar approach, either we do as you proposed, or we also rename indexSelector.\n\nBoth are select so maybe we should have `options`, `value` and `text` for both of them, would be easier?\n",
    "created_at": "2015-10-22T14:04:45Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/331#issuecomment-150235000",
    "id": 150235000,
